@version 0.1.0
@title kvex — approximate k-NN vector search on the BEAM
@doc

kvex provides an Erlang/OTP interface to the TurboQuant algorithm
(Google Research, ICLR 2026) for approximate k-nearest-neighbour
vector search. Vectors are compressed to 2–4 bits per coordinate
without any training phase, and search runs on SIMD kernels through a
`rustler' NIF over the `turbovec' Rust crate.

See the {@link kvex} module for the full public API.

